Peter Jennings, the iconic ABC News anchor, revealed his battle with lung cancer, opting for chemotherapy over surgery.
Despite his illness, he remains committed to anchoring "World News Tonight" when possible.
Colleagues express support and admiration for his dedication to journalism.
Jennings' decision to share his diagnosis publicly is seen as a source of inspiration for others facing similar challenges.
The news has deeply impacted ABC News, with executives and staff rallying around Jennings during this difficult time.
His legacy as a respected journalist and beloved figure in the industry is evident in the outpouring of support.
